// Mesa Vista Pharmacy — the fictional, resettable demo tenant.
//
// Everything here is invented: three Nevada locations, fifteen staff with
// @mesavistarx.com addresses (a domain that receives no mail), six weeks of
// schedule anchored to the Monday of the CURRENT week at runtime, one
// engine-real deficiency story, and compliance snapshots generated by the
// same engine the app uses.
//
// The deficiency story (current week, Thursday, Henderson): Dr. Sunita
// Patel left at 2:00 PM on a family emergency and the float pharmacist,
// Dr. Owen Fitzgerald, was held up at Spring Valley until 4:00 PM — so
// from 2:00–4:00 the technicians kept the counter open with no pharmacist
// on duty. The ratio engine flags exactly those slots deficient; one
// isolated day, so no 3-consecutive-day board trigger.
//
// Shared by scripts/seed-mesa-vista.ts (CLI) and the admin console's
// "Restore demo data" action — so it deliberately has NO "server-only"
// import and uses relative paths (tsx-friendly).

